        name: "Anecdote: Ⅳ",
        unlock: "Character Reaches Lv. 50",
        text: 'A plague once swept across Huaxu.\nIt endured without respite, claiming countless lives — and among them was the last Zhuyou of the Hall of Ephemerality.\nShe laboured tirelessly among the masses, her fingers grown numb from invoking the Art of Ephemerality without rest. With each life she drew back from the brink, her own edged ever closer to its destined end.\nPeople praised her selflessness; they honoured her devotion. Yet few understood the price of such mercy.\nAnd each person she healed, grateful beyond expression, would murmur the same gentle blessing: "Good things will come to good people."',
