        text: "Yale had long believed he would be forever friendless. The Alchemy Academy was a place of cold sterility — corridors bathed in harsh white light, researchers clad in stark white lab coats, and towering stacks of experiment reports on every desk. This monochrome existence draped over him, filling the days of his memory.\nIn this lifeless setting, Yale yearned for a friend. His artistic skills were limited — the best he could manage was a ball, or rather, a somewhat misshapen circle. Initially, the white light reflecting off the white paper made the circle seem cold and uninviting, until Yale added a splash of orange, which was the first vivid colour in his life.",
