        text: "You stood on the balcony where Parsifal used to practice his singing.\nBefore there were heavy theatre curtains to separate him from the audience — this was his stage. Dawn served as his spotlight. The street below, his backdrop. Snow-laden wind, his orchestra. Birdsong, his harmony.\nThough the floor had been swept clean, a single wild sprout had pushed its way up between the tiles — perhaps whoever came to tend the place hadn't the heart to pull it out. You brushed your fingers gently across its blade, as if to offer a silent wish: May you grow strong, for the one who no longer can.",
